Author : Mason Hart (mphart)

main.c : a program to create a navicable world full of maps that connect via paths

map.c : a program to create an 80x21 map with multiple biomes, north-south and east-west paths, 
and a pokecenter and pokemart.

Running this program : 'make run' in the terminal
If you want to set the number of trainers: 'make build' and './main --numtrainers {x}' in the terminal

Terrain Generation : The terrain is represented by a character array of size 80*21. 
When a terrain is generated, seeds are randomly placed around the map, with certain types being more common than others. 
Next, spots are randomly selected and if they are not blank they will fill the surrounding nonempty squares. 
Next, the border of rock is generated. Then, two paths are placed at random, linking up to nearby maps if applicable.
Finally, up to one pokemart and up to one pokecenter is placed along the path.

Legend :
# path
% rock
: tall grass
. short grass
^ tree
~ water
M pokemart
C pokecenter

world.c : a program to consolidate all maps in the world and keep track of high-level game logic

character.c : a program to represent the PC and their rivals that can spawn in the world. Provides the functionality for finding
the distance maps from the character's position to every other square on the map. Contains functionality for moving NPCs.

Adversarial Trainers : Trainers have been added to the game. A handful of them are added to every map, each with its own movement patterns
Legend :
r rival - moves toward the player
h hiker - moves toward the player, can traverse most terrain
p pacer - paces in one direction, turning around when stuck
w wanderer - moves in one direction, turning around at the edge of the biome
s sentry - stays put
e explorer - same as wanderer, but crosses biome borders
